  Tokyo  Electric Power Co. said smoke
was seen rising from the building of the No. 3 reactors at its
stricken nuclear plant in Fukushima north of Tokyo at about 3:55
p.m. local time. Workers were evacuated from the building,
spokesman Kaoru Yoshida said at a briefing in Tokyo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
